In a first for Africa, two Russian bombers are expected to land at Waterkloof air base in Tshwane today. They are capable of launching nuclear missiles. Courtesy #DStv403 MOSCOW - Russia will land two nuclear-capable strategic bombers in South Africa on Wednesday, Interfax news agency cited South Africa's military as saying. Russia's defence ministry said on Monday that two Tupolev Tu-160 bombers were being sent to South Africa on a first-ever flight to develop bilateral military cooperation. READ:Â SA engineer to compete at World Skills Competition in Russia The flight comes amid a push by Moscow for influence on the African continent.